; DOMAIN: measure-theory [CLOSED, derived 2026-07-24] ; Claim: a pre-measure on a ring R extends to a measure on the generated sigma-algebra. ; Structure: (ring R) (pre-measure mu countably-additive-on-R) (outer-measure mu-star via covers) ; Result: Caratheodory-measurable sets form a sigma-algebra on which mu-star is a complete measure extending mu. ; Minimal: outer-measure + Caratheodory-criterion => complete sigma-additive extension. ; Bridge: belief-mass over an event-ring extends uniquely to the generated evidence sigma-algebra. (= (extend $mu) (restrict (outer $mu) caratheodory-measurable))